text: ADQ may refer to: * Abductor digiti quinti (disambiguation) * Action démocratique du Québec, defunct political party in Quebec, Canada * American Dairy Queen Corporation, American franchiser of Dairy Queen restaurants * Dangme language, a Kwa language of Ghana * Kodiak Airport, Kodiak, Alaska, United States * Average daily quantity, a measure of drug consumption similar to defined daily dose * Average delay in queue, a measure of queuing delay
title: ADQ
